script = ExtResource("3_hfc7j")
category = 2
text = "The Great Masters are an independent body of five capable mages, each considered the peak in one of the five elements. They are elected by an unanimous vote of the other Great Masters, including the departing one if he lives. Once raised to the title a Great Master will symbolically leave their old life behind, exchanging their last name for that of their element. The Great Masters, in order of seniority are: Draco Thunderblood, Gofa Waterblood, Rakinji Windblood, Leon Earthblood and Zoyana Fireblood.

The Great Masters have been part of Zengefian culture as long as the country. They were established during the tumultous Manywar Period, before the formation of the Prasedi. During the wars, there was a need for strong teachers of magic in each element and so one of the clan leaders, Golden Losa (unnecessary character but oh well), recruited some of the strongest mages in the country to serve her. Losa named them the Great Masters and instructed them to teach her most promising soldiers. They obliged and over time developed comradery amongst each other, and so once Losa died they stuck together. Tales of five talented teachers spread amongst the nobility and even the common folk, many ambitious mages came to them for guidance. The volume of students coming to them was massive, they could not take them all as students, and so took only the most talented. After a few decades, and multiple generations of students, the name of the Great Masters spread far and wide with the help of the students. They saw the value in continuing their tradition and so decided that upon the death of one of them, the other would be elected democratically amongst the four survivors. This tradition persists to this day.

The duties of a modern day Great Master have been quite similar for centuries, they were created to train soldiers and now train students. While not recognized as an official body, they are often involved in politics, resolving both national and international crises easily, due to their nature as a small specialised force with lots of talented mages, the students, being available for any tasks where manpower is necessary. Obligations of a student also have persisted for a long time, while they vary from Great Master to Great Master, most are expected to live near to their master and hold daily sessions which include sparring, philosophy and understanding of magic. How long a Great Masters student can study for is not limited, similarly to the amount of students, shown by the record of 93 by Pingui Windblood, it is however typical for certain elements to maintain a specific range. Windbloods typically have the most, followed by Waterbloods, Earthbloods and then Firebloods which often stick to 2-4 students. Thunderbloods have only had a single student for at least the lasts two centuries due to Clifftowns, a town which nurtures Thundermages, influence. Every single Thunderblood in the last two centuries has come from Clifftown and it is typical that a successor is chosen instantly, right after a Thunderblood's celeberation ceremony.

While appearing united outwardly, there is often quite a lot of bickering inwardly. In the current generation of Great Masters, Zoyana Fireblood's resistance to taking students has caused quite a lot of strife between her and Rakinji Windblood, who sees it as a duty as sacred as the First Man. Draco Thunderblood has a one-sided rivalry with Gofa Waterblood, who is often considered the strongest of the Great Masters and their unofficial leader. Leon Earthblood is quiet and keeps alone, but the unusual lifelike movements of his golems has not gone unnoticed by Rakinji, who is currently investigating the matter. Among the students there is a similar level of discord, the ages and backgrounds of the students vary widely and many of the younger ones are affected by the disposition of their master, and either attempt to emulate it or tend to become similar to them simply by proximity over decades. Currently Rakinji students are often dismissed, as the weakest of the bunch while Gofa's are idolised, due to their masters status. Maian, Draco's only student, is not very diplomatic and it is not uncommon to see her boxing Lola Tenos, one of Gofa's students who enjoys leading on some of Leon's younger students. Overall the students respect strength, shown by your mastery of elements, more than any other factors such as whether you were born noble or your wealth.

Once a Great Master deems he did everything to help a student grow that he could, they are released. Many organisations seek past students for any magically-intensive job, as it's an almost guarantee they will outshine any of your other workers. However, the students themself, often are unsatisfied using their magic for mundane tasks after all their training and so in the past joined the Seamages, or monster clearing parties near the Unim desert, but now are congregating in the newly formed Mage Army of Zengef. While only Huff Perkot and Luxi Bellam from the upper crust of the Mage Army are students, there are innumerous Captains, Chiefs and Noble soldiers and officers that were once students. Some other notable past students are Egref Lecti, Jules Cupid, Silent Ron, Lank Follas and Acuti Redsnake. The current generation of students are some of the strongest mages to date, especially Maian, Panon and Joras who are the expected successors to their respective Great Masters, and many are anticipating that their strength will exceed that of their masters, no small feat when competing against the likes of Draco, Leon and Gofa."
id = 93
name = "Zengef Great Masters"
gdscript = ExtResource("1_isjie")
saved_data = ExtResource("2_llour")
